value.title: Colin Powell calls for Trump's resignation 'as quickly as possible': 'He should be totally ashamed of himself'
value.excerpt: Former U.S. State Secretary Colin Powell, a Republican, called for President Trump's resignation "as soon as possible."

value.title: Kurtz: 'No president has been able to dominate the media, social media, culture more than Trump'
value.excerpt: President Trump is one of the most influential presidents in United States history,” "Media Buzz" host Howard Kurtz said Friday.

value.title: U.S. labor federation urges Trump removal, calling him 'danger' to nation
value.excerpt: The board of a labor federation of more than 50 unions representing 12.5 million workers called for U.S. President Donald Trump's resignation or removal from office.

value.title: GOP Sen. Ben Sasse says there is 'brokenness' in Trump's soul, refuses to rule out impeachment
value.excerpt: GOP Sen. Ben Sasse said Friday he is willing to consider articles of impeachment against President Trump if they are introduced by the House of Representatives following a violent mob attack by pro-Trump supporters on the nation's Capitol earlier this week.

value.title: Trump's failure to 'call off mob' at Capitol riots was 'breaking point': Alyssa Farah
value.excerpt: Former White House communications director Alyssa Farah criticized President Trump for his actions Wednesday amid the "heartbreaking" Capitol Hill riots that "crossed a line."

value.title: Trump says his supporters will still have a 'giant voice,' won't be 'disrespected'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday said his supporters will still have a “giant voice” and would not be “disrespected” after he leaves the White House.

value.title: Dems 'caught up in their own mob mentality,' trying to 'blame everything on Trump': Hurt
value.excerpt: While Republicans look inward in the aftermath of the Capitol Hill riots after President Trump's address Wednesday, Democrats are adding to the division, Fox News contributor Charles Hurt argued Friday.

value.title: DeWine does not support Arts Council appointee comments; media owner called Kamala Harris a 'whore'
value.excerpt: Ohio Gov. Mike DeWine, through a spokeswoman, condemned comments made by Ohio Arts Council board member Susan Allan Block.

value.title: Melania Trump and adult Trump children avoid the spotlight after one of nation's darkest days
value.excerpt: As thousands of pro-Trump supporters streamed into Washington, DC, Wednesday headed first to the Ellipse to hear President Donald Trump speak, and then to the United States Capitol to lay siege to the epicenter of American democracy, first lady Melania Trump was doing a photo shoot at the White House.

value.title: NBA: Los Angeles Lakers hope to meet President Joe Biden but champions lose at Spurs
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Lakers hope to re-establish the tradition of NBA champions visiting the president of the United States.

value.title: Elaine Chao, Betsy DeVos step down from Trump Cabinet following Capitol storming
value.excerpt: Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao became the first Trump Cabinet member to resign in the wake of Wednesday's storming of the Capitol by the president's supporters.

value.title: Biden Picks California Official Isabel Guzman to Head SBA
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden announced Thursday that he picked California official Isabel Guzman to lead the Small Business Administration.

value.title: Donald Trump recognises 'new administration' after US Capitol riot – video

value.title: Trump official merchandise stores removed by Shopify
value.excerpt: The e-commerce platform Shopify said Thursday that it has terminated stores affiliated with President Donald Trump.

value.title: WSJ Opinion: Trump Erases His Legacy

value.title: Hear why Klobuchar fist-bumped Pence after Electoral certification
value.excerpt: Sen. Amy Klobuchar (D-MN), tells CNN's Chris Cuomo about the moment Congress finalized President-elect Joe Biden's victory, and about why she chose to fist-bump Vice President Mike Pence after he read the election results.

value.title: Trump's Education Secretary Betsy DeVos submits resignation
value.excerpt: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos has submitted her resignation, making her the second Cabinet member to resign over President Donald Trump's response to the mob breaching the US Capitol on Wednesday, according to an official.

value.title: Haley tells GOP not to ‘shy away’ from Trump-era gains, but calls his recent conduct 'deeply disappointing'
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Thursday hailed the “extraordinary gains” for the United States during President Trump’s time in office and warned Republicans not to “shy away” from them -- while at the same time calling his post-Election Day conduct “deeply disappointing.”

value.title: Several Cabinet secretaries informally discuss invoking 25th Amendment but Pence 'highly unlikely' to pursue
value.excerpt: Inquiries about invoking the 25th Amendment have been coming into Vice President Mike Pence's advisers and those discussions have been under way, a source close to the vice president said Thursday, with several Cabinet secretaries informally discussing the matter.

value.title: 'Double standard': Biden, Black lawmakers and activists decry police response to attack on US Capitol
value.excerpt: Civil rights leaders blasted police for their response to an attack on the U.S. Capitol compared to clashes between Black Lives protesters and police.

value.title: Trump condemns 'heinous attack' on Capitol, calls for 'healing and reconciliation'
value.excerpt: President Trump condemned Wednesday’s “heinous attack” on the Capitol by his supporters and called for a moment of healing.

value.title: Biden quiet on 25th Amendment calls; tells Pence, Cabinet, Congress to 'act as they see fit'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has stayed mum amid calls from Democrats to invoke the 25th Amendment or pursue articles of impeachment to thwart the last two weeks of the Trump presidency.
